@startuml
top to bottom direction

actor "End‑User (Mobile User)" as User
actor "Third‑Party KYC Service" as KYC_Svc
actor "Bank Back-Office" as Bank_BO

package "User personal data" as USER {
    usecase "Populate necessary info" as StartReg
}

package "KYC processes" as KYC {
    usecase "Invoke KYC Service" as InvokeKYC
}
package "Bank‑Specific" as BANK {
    usecase "Create Account Record" as CreateAcc
    usecase "Assign User‑ID" as AssignID
    usecase "Inform user about KYC results" as KYC_Inform
    usecase "Process duplicates" as KYC_Dups
}

User --> StartReg : Fill form
StartReg  --> InvokeKYC : <<include>>
InvokeKYC --> KYC_Svc : <<perform>>
InvokeKYC --> KYC_Inform : <<extend>>
InvokeKYC --> CreateAcc : <<include>>
InvokeKYC --> AssignID : <<include>>
AssignID  --> Bank_BO : <<perform>>
CreateAcc --> Bank_BO : <<perform>>
KYC_Inform   --> Bank_BO : <<perform>>
KYC_Dups --> Bank_BO : <<perform>>

'Additional notes
note left of StartReg
  • The mobile app **does not collect or store** any personal data.  
  • All documents / personal identifiers are forwarded **only** to the third‑party KYC service.
end note

note right of InvokeKYC
  • The KYC service validates identity using its own secure pipeline.
end note

note top of KYC_Inform
  • Bank informs the user about the verification outcome (success / failure).
end note

@enduml
